misconceptions.student_belief:
If I write:

if (grade >= 60)
    if (grade >= 70)
        System.out.println("passing");
else
    System.out.println("F");

then the else corresponds to the first if (grade >= 60).

misconceptions.remediation_hint:
Add braces any time you nest if/else, and rewrite this logic as a clear if/else-if/else chain. For example:

if (grade >= 70) {
    System.out.println("passing");
} else {
    System.out.println("F");
}

Then extend this pattern for A/B/C/D ranges.

